@NODE "Purpose"
PURPOSE
=======

GSD shows the operation of various sorting algorithms. It displays
the comparisons and movements of the elements to be sorted.
Note: the program does not serve to compare the efficiency (e.g.
the speed) of the algorithms! Many of the implementations of the
algorithms used here are not optimized. Some of the algorithms are
changed in a way to better illustrate its mode of operation, which,
however, sometimes slows down the algorithms (see below).
Have a look at the books in the @{"references" LINK "References"} if you want to compare the
algorithms. This program simply wants to show @{b}how@{ub} the algorithms
work, not how efficient they are.
@ENDNODE


